Of all of the maps that I have completed, de_arcis is by far my favorite. I have run hundreds of hours of tests on the map and have purged it of all known glitches or defects. This is far and away the best temple map that I have seen in existence and I am proud to be its creator.

The atmosphere of de_arcis is truly unique. If I were to write a background story for this map it would run something like this:

"On January 3, 2008, a satelite owned by a private corporation in Southern California tracking an abnormally large sandstorm discovered what appeared to be the ruins of a stone structure in the midst of the Khadarin Desert on the ancient road that once joined Eastern Magpyr and the trading port at Khapor. Analysts caught their first glimpse of the structure when they noticed the sun reflecting off of an object that might be a metal dome. Word got out about the discovery and a small sect of Dangal Elitists, the radical group likely responsible for the Cairo Central Bank Bombings earlier this month, claimed that the coordinates of the discovery closely correspond to the location of the the Great Temple of Arcis, which was recorded by their own ancient writings as having been buried in an unprecedented sandstorm around 150 BC. The Dangals immediately dispatched a militant task force to take control of the temple and were the first to step inside. Seven local governments staked joint claim to the ruins and, expecting resistance, dispatched an elite unit comprised of counter-terrorist components from agencies of all seven countries. A confrontation is inevitable."

de_arcis is an elemental temple representing the 4 elements, earth, fire, water, and air. The earth and water altars are bombsites. The air altar when jumped on will lift you up to a sniper loft (if you are skilled enough to figure out how it works). The fire altar and statue room are the main confrontation points. As far as I know the map has no CT/T leaning- it should be perfectly balanced with 3 obvious exits from CT and 3 obvious exits from T.  The map as you can tell is asymetrical and multi-leveled, quite an accomplishment for a well balanced map.

A dust-like map that was originally made for Counter-Strike. The architecture is very simple (hence why it was made for Counter-Strike) but it recieved a little overhaul for Counter-Strike Source. The main 'feeling' of the map is archeology, hence the name 'de_archeo'. Terrorists have to bomb one of two valuable spots to win.

The map features both outside and underground spots, 2 sniping ranges, a lot of close-combat spots and very quick and intense rounds. Two bomb sites are available: (A) One in an underground tunnel where precious vases and crates of uncalculable price lay still unopened by archeologists who fled the region because of terrorist threats, or (B) an open archeology field where discovery of precious artifacts is imminent in a marked ground section.

*NOTE!* This map was made for Counter-Strike (1.6) but I modified it so it will now only work for CS:Source. The architecture is very simple, so bear with it. I am currently fixing some minor issues with the map, but it's already 100% completed. I'm already working on a more detailed maps which will use displacements and the full power of the new source engine, de_archeo2.

Welcome to Apriveruca - School of Conjuring

As one might expect in a school of conjuring, there are many strange and wondrous items to view and find.  However, the Ts have decided to blast the school back to oblivion.

Look for teleports, secret passages, hidden doors and weapon caches.
See if you can find the infirmary, the rainbow globe, the re-direction room, the
malfunctioning beamer, the map room, the way to the tree perch, or the path to the tower balcony.  There is even a blue bottle of bubbles.

"Underground sources say that the curator of The Sanctuary of Apollo, an important Mediterranean archaeological park/museum, has allegedly borrowed money from the local Mafia to finance a new exhibit. The Mafia family has accused the museum of refusing to repay their loan, and has subsequently sent in threats to the members of the museum's administration. It is feared that the Mafia intends to bomb a part of the museum to avenge their betrayal."

de Apollo is a medium-sized demolition map arranged in a 'four-square' layout. Its setting is a fictional archaeology park and museum in the Mediterranean. The ruins in this level is based on a combination of ancient roman sites. The major areas are as follows:

Museum Entrance- CT Spawn
Roman Basilica - Bomb A
Street and Coutyard - Central connection to all areas
Museum Gallery - Bomb B
Roman Ruins - T Spawn

More information here:
http://evanbatson.com/projectdeapollo.html

Basically this ia a bomb defusal map where the terrorists' gain is to plant a bomb in the area where the two APCs are located, to destroy them. The Counter Terrorists' goal is to prevent the Terrorists from planting and detonating the C4. The Counter Terrorists have a large amount of sniper points to hinder the terrorists from getting to the APC, whilst the Terrorists have a large amount of weapons ready for them. This map would be best played with at least 10 players on each team, and would be at it's peak with 64 players.
